==English==

===Pronunciation===
*tû(r)d, /tɜː(r)d/, /<tt>t3:(r)d</tt>/

===Noun===
'''turd''' (''plural:'' [[turds]])

# (''Vulgar'') a piece of solid animal or human excrement. "I went to the toilet to drop a [[turd]]".
# a [[pejorative]] term, typically directed at a person. Whether it should be considered an especially vulgar insult is subject to judgment, but certainly it would have a broader acceptability than many vulgarities in common use today.

